	   <tr><td colspan=2>Personally, when I hit level 30, I stopped trying to gain levels for about two weeks, and began to buy / sell items in GFay and EC.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are patient, you can find cheap items and sell them for twice as much a few days later.  (A good example would be a Blackened Crystalline Robe for 500 PP, which you can later sell for 1000 PP.)  You'll be quite successful if you make even a 25% return on your investments.  Although it seems tedious, you can make an amazing amount of money over a short period of time.  Try to deal in caster gear because you can wear the equipment as you try to sell it, but that doesn't mean you should pass up on great deals for melee/WIS gear if you see them.<br><br>Rascarcapac, level 30 Mage, Xev Server.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
